{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"60ab4b44-b258-46be-94c4-2436b7378914","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"30c2229d-e767-4213-908d-6ae01b1d116d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"4821:2766CC:805161:938FB8:69FBE8E7"},"id":"8c02b677-d015-47c1-af59-b55e1dd889c9","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:20:44.473Z","parentId":"16acc769-d7cf-4d0f-87a0-54d72f0852ca"}
